":"1256","1244":"1244","1211":"1211","1210":"1210","1232":"1232","6 September 1195":"6 September 1195","by 1216":"1232","about 1210":"about 1210","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","of Cadbury, Somerset, England":"North Cadbury, Somerset, England","Somerset, Inglaterra, United Kingdom":"Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Cadbury, Devon, Inglaterra, United Kingdom":"Cadbury, Devon, England, United Kingdom","North Cadbury, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"North Cadbury, Somerset, England, United Kingdom","Neufmarché, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France":"Neufmarché, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Matilda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Matilda was born on 6 January 1180, in Neufmarché, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France. She married James de Newmarch on 6 September 1195, in Cadbury, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. She died on 21 October 1256, in North Cadbury, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 76."},"et":{"6 January 1180–21 October 1256":"6. jaanuar 1180–21. oktoober 1256","1170–1232":"1170–1232","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1211–1244":"1211–1244","1180–1256":"1180–1256","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","21 October 1256":"21. oktoober 1256","6 January 1180":"6. jaanuar 1180","Abt 1211":"umbes 1211","1256":"1256","1244":"1244","1211":"1211","1210":"1210","1232":"1232","6 September 1195":"6. september 1195","by 1216":"1232","about 1210":"umbes 1210","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","of Cadbury, Somerset, England":"North Cadbury, Somerset, England","Somerset, Inglaterra, United Kingdom":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cadbury, Devon, Inglaterra, United Kingdom":"Cadbury, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","North Cadbury, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"North Cadbury, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Neufmarché, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France":"Neufmarché, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"6 January 1180–21 October 1256":"6. tammikuuta 1180–21. lokakuuta 1256","1170–1232":"1170–1232","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1211–1244":"1211–1244","1180–1256":"1180–1256","1170":"1170","1180":"1180","21 October 1256":"21. lokakuuta 1256","6 January 1180":"6. tammikuuta 1180","Abt 1211":"noin 1211","1256":"1256","1244":"1244","1211":"1211","1210":"1210","1232":"1232","6 September 1195":"6. syyskuuta 1195","by 1216":"1232","about 1210":"noin 1210","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","of Cadbury, Somerset, England":"North Cadbury, Somerset, England","Somerset, Inglaterra, United Kingdom